import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['US_Gross', 'Worldwide_Gross']]
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='US_Gross', y='Worldwide_Gross')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Production_Budget'] = data['Production_Budget'].astype(float)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Production_Budget', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Production_Budget'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating']]
    sns.boxplot(data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Running_Time_min'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Running_Time_min'], format='%M').dt.minute
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Running_Time_min', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['Running_Time_min'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['MPAA_Rating'] = data['MPAA_Rating'].astype('category')
    chart = sns.countplot(x='MPAA_Rating', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
